column5: description
The Prince of Denmark, son of the late King Hamlet and nephew of the present King Claudius.
A young noblewoman of Denmark, daughter of Polonius, sister of Laertes, and potential wife of Prince Hamlet.
The female protagonist of William Shakespeare's romantic tragedy Romeo and Juliet.
The male protagonist and one of two protagonists of William Shakespeare's romantic tragedy Romeo and Juliet.
The title character of William Shakespeare's tragedy Othello, the Moor of Venice.
The wife of Othello, a Venetian military leader.
The title character and protagonist of William Shakespeare's tragedy Macbeth.
The wife of the play's protagonist, Macbeth, a Scottish nobleman.
The title character and protagonist of William Shakespeare's tragedy King Lear.
The youngest daughter of King Lear and the only one who truly loves him.
The protagonist of William Shakespeare's play The Tempest.
The daughter of Prospero, the protagonist of William Shakespeare's play The Tempest.
The title character and protagonist of William Shakespeare's tragedy Antony and Cleopatra.
The female protagonist of William Shakespeare's tragedy Antony and Cleopatra.
A comic character in William Shakespeare's plays Henry IV, Part 1 and Henry IV, Part 2.
The title character and protagonist of William Shakespeare's play Henry V.
The protagonist of William Shakespeare's tragedy Titus Andronicus.
The Queen of the Goths and the antagonist of William Shakespeare's tragedy Titus Andronicus.
The son of William Shakespeare and Anne Hathaway, and the only one of their three children to survive infancy.
The wife of William Shakespeare, and the mother of their three children.
